<HEADLINE>
Leaders of developing Muslim countries to meet March 1-2
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   DHAKA , Bangladesh (AP) _ Bangladesh will host a two-day summit
on March 1 for eight developing Muslim countries, the second since
the so-called D-8 was formed last year in Istanbul, the government
announced Tuesday.
	   Indonesia, Iran, Egypt, Malaysia, Nigeria, Pakistan and Turkey
will attend the summit, Foreign Secretary Mustafizur Rahman said.
	   The summit was postponed in November after devastating floods in
Bangladesh.
