<HEADLINE>
Hong Kong shares close higher in light trading
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HONG KONG (AP) _ Hong Kong stocks ended slightly higher Tuesday
with few shares traded as investors stayed away for the holiday
season.
	   The blue-chip Hang Seng Index rose 55.83 points, or 0.5 percent,
to close at 10,225.97.
	   Trading volume was thin, with some fund managers switching to
other markets in preparation for the inauguration of the single
European currency _ the euro _ on Monday, said Felix Ngai of Sun
Hung Kai Commodities Ltd.
	   Selling in big property shares in the afternoon gave a late
boost to the weak market turnover, which hit 1.33 billion Hong Kong
dollars (U.S. dlrs 170 million) _ barely higher than Monday's
six-year low of 1.22 billion Hong Kong dollars (U.S. dlrs 156
million).
	   The day's biggest gainers were banking giant HSBC Holdings, up
2.00 Hong Kong dollars to close at 197.00; China Light, up 0.50 at
39.40; and Cheung Kong Infrastructure, up 0.40 at 17.75.
	   Conglomerate Swire Pacific ``A'' was up 0.10 at 35.70.
	   Among the losers were Henderson Land, down 0.40 at 40.70;
Hutchison Whampoa, down 0.25 at 54.75; Sun Hung Kai Properties,
down 0.25 at 57.25; and Cheung Kong Holdings, down 0.25 at 56.50.
	   Hong Kong's flag carrier Cathay Pacific gained 0.15 to 7.65. 	   
