w1071 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SKorea-Trade     12-29 0153
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SKorea-Trade </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
South Korea posts dlrs 3.33 billion current account surplus in
</HEADLINE>
November

<TEXT>
	   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) _ Sharply falling imports helped South
Korea post a dlrs 3.33 billion current account surplus in November,
the central Bank of Korea said in a preliminary report Tuesday.
	   November's gain pushed the nation's combined current account
surplus for the first eleven months of this year to dlrs 37.24
billion, compared with a deficit of dlrs 11.75 billion during the
same period last year.
	   November's gain was the nation's 13th consecutive monthly gain.
It compared with a dlrs 860 million surplus during the same month
last year.
	   Exports fell 4.5 percent to dlrs 11.6 billion but imports
plunged 29.7 percent to dlrs 8.1 billion.
	   Imports have dropped sharply in recent months as businesses
slashed capital investment and consumers spent less amid the
country's economic crisis. 	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-SKorea-Trade; CT:i; 
(REG:ASIA;)
(REG:ENGL;)
