<HEADLINE>
Businessman brutally killed in Ukraine
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A wealthy regional official was brutally
gunned down in western Ukraine in an apparent organized crime
contract killing, officials said Tuesday.
	   Two unidentified killers with automatic guns fired dozens of
bullets at Mykhailo Tokar, member of a regional council, as he
parked his car near his home in the city of Mukachevo late Friday.
	   Tokar, 37, died almost immediately of multiple wounds and the
killers escaped after discarding their weapons on a nearby street,
Vasyl Bonkalo, a police spokesman in Mukachevo told The Associated
Press. The killings bore all the hallmarks of a contract killing.
	   Several newspapers said Tuesday the murder might have been
organized by one of the region's criminal gangs and linked to
Tokar's alleged involvement in smuggling operations.
	   Tokar allegedly controlled the smuggling of cars and alcohol
from neighboring eastern European states and exports to these
countries of cheap labor, the daily Segodnya said.
	   Ukraine's Zakarpattia region, which borders Hungary, Slovakia
and Romania, is a major route for smuggling goods to Ukraine.
	   (vl/ren)
