<SLUG> BC-Sports-Skiing-Burtin </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
French skier injured in downhill spill
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With BORMIO-Men-Downhill &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BORMIO, Italy (AP) _ Nicolas Burtin hurt his right knee in a
high-speed spill during Tuesday's World Cup downhill race here,
continuing a streak of injuries and misfortune dogging the French
men's team this season.
	   Burtin fell and crashed into the safety nets, twisting his knee,
at the Orso corner, in the upper part of the icy and twisty Stelvio
course.
	   Team officials said Burtin will undergo medical examinations in
France Wednesday to determine the extent of the injury.
	   The 26-year-old French skier, winner of a World Cup downhill
last season, already had suffered a bad knee injury _ a torn
ligament _ at the same Italian track two years ago.
	   Three other French downhillers, including Olympic champion
Jean-Luc Cretier, suffered season ending knee injuries in the two
previous World Cup downhills at Val Gardena earlier this month.
