<SLUG> BC-Russia-Oil </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Russia's oil production to total 303.5 million tons in
</HEADLINE>
1998 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russia produced an estimated 303.5 million metric
tons of oil in 1998, and exported 134 million metric tons, the Fuel
and Energy Ministry said Tuesday.
	   Oil exports are Russia's main revenue earner, and the
cash-strapped government has been trying to keep up exports,
despite the slide of world oil prices.
	   This year's exports will mark a 6.3-percent increase from 1997,
the Fuel and Energy Ministry said, according to the Interfax news
agency. But revenues were down considerably, officials have said.
	   Next year, Russia is expected to produce between 284 million
metric tons and 296 million metric tons of oil _ down nearly 5
percent from 1998, the ministry said.
	   Russia will export between 108 million metric tons and 120
million metric tons of oil next year, it said.
	   (ad/ml)
</TEXT>
