<SLUG> BC-Czech-Refugees </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Twenty-nine illegal immigrants found in a van
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ Twenty-nine illegal immigrants
from Iraq and Afghanistan were found hidden in a van Monday during
a routine traffic control, the news agency CTK reported Tuesday.
	   The agency quoted police spokeswoman Dagmar Bartonikova as
saying that driver of the van escaped when police stopped the car
and was not yet detained.
	   Bartonikova said that the refugees asked for political asylum
and were placed in a refugee camp.
	   The Czech Republic is becoming a popular transit destination for
refugees.
	   More than 33,000 illegal immigrants have been caught in the
Czech Republic this year, but only a fraction have asked for
asylum, as the final hoped-for destination for most of them is
Germany.
	   (nr/gj)
