<HEADLINE>
Swedish priest jailed for attempting to smuggle 2 people into
</HEADLINE>
Denmark &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) _ A Swedish priest was sentenced to 30
days in jail on Tuesday after admitting he attempted to smuggle two
men into Denmark.
	   The 62-year-old Lutheran priest, whose identity was not publicly
disclosed, was arrested late Monday in Nakskov, southern Denmark,
upon arrival from Germany by ferry. During a random check, police
found the men, who were believed to be from Iraq, hidden in his car
trunk.
	   The priest told the court in the town of Maribo that his motives
were humanitarian. He picked up the men in Austria and Germany,
Danish radio reported.
	   The court banned him from entering Denmark for the next five
years.
	   The two refugees likely would be returned to Germany.
	   (jo-ewm)
