<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Death Sentence </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
China sentences revenge bank robber to death
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ A former postal service employee who killed a
bank assistant while mounting a revenge robbery on a bank was
sentenced to death Tuesday by a Beijing court, official media said.
	   Guo Hui, 20, was dismissed from the postal service in October
for incompetency, the state-run Xinhua News Agency said. The next
month, on Nov. 14, Guo broke into a postal savings bank in Daxing
county, in Beijing's southern suburbs, in revenge, it said.
	   He killed Zhang Li, a female bank assistant, and stole about
5,000 yuan (dlrs 600), Xinhua said.
	   Guo was sentenced to death by the Beijing No.1 Intermediate
People's Court. His girlfriend, 18-year-old Ruan Fang, was
sentenced to three years imprisonment for giving false testimony
and covering up for Gao, it said. 	   
</TEXT>
