<SLUG> BC-Lithuania-Sabonis </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NBA center returns home to play for national champion during
</HEADLINE>
lockout &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VILNIUS, Lithuania (AP) _ Portland Trail Blazers center Arvydas
Sabonis on Tuesday joined Lithuania's national champion Zalgiras
and will play for them in the European league while the NBA lockout
lasts, team officials said.
	   He signed a five-month contract, but both sides said he could
return to the U.S. basketball league on short notice when its games
resume.
	   His first game is scheduled for Jan. 7 in Belgrade, Yugoslavia,
against Red Star.
	   (ld-ewm)
</TEXT>
