<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Bosnia-Germany </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
German General arrives for a one-week visit to Bosnia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SARAJEVO, Bosnia-Herzegovina (AP) _ The commanding general of
the German Fourth Corps, Lt. Gen. Hans-Peter von Kirchbach, arrived
in Bosnia on Tuesday to spend New Year's eve with his soldiers
serving in Bosnia.
	   Gen. Kirchbach became known as the ``Oder-General'' because of
his role in the rescue efforts in the fight against the worst
flooding on the Oder river this century that occurred in 1997.
	   The general will be visiting various German barracks in Sarajevo
and Mostar for a week.
	   According to the press release issued by the German contingent
in Bosnia, Gen. Kirchbach will be looking at the mission and
readiness of the German soldiers here.
	   Some 3,000 German soldiers serving in Bosnia as a part of
32,000-strong international military contingent.
	   (asd/acr/rr)
</TEXT>
