<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Self-Immolation </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian miner dies following self-immolation
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A Ukrainian miner who set himself on fire
two weeks before over unpaid wages died in a hospital despite
intensive medical treatment, a news report said Tuesday.
	   Oleksandr Mykhalevych, 35, immolated himself Dec. 14 in front of
the regional government headquarters in the city of Luhansk to
protest months of overdue wages.
	   He was hospitalized with burns covering nearly half of his body
and died late Monday, despite several skin transplant operations,
the Interfax news agency said.
	   Mykhalevych was among 200 miners from the city of Krasnodon who
had picketed the regional administration building in Luhansk since
the summer to demand overdue salaries.
	   The protesters finally received the money owed them several days
after Mykhalevych set himself ablaze.
	   Dozens of mines throughout Ukraine were protesting for months
this year, but the cash-strapped government failed to allocate more
subsidies for the ailing industry and repay the wage debt.
	   Miners are currently owed about dlrs 2.3 billion hryvna (dlrs
670 million), and the debt has been growing.
	   (vl/ml)
</TEXT>
