<SLUG> BC-Germany-Gorbachev </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Gorbachev says he lost his money in Russian financial crisis
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MUNICH, Germany (AP) _ Former Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev
says in an interview published Tuesday that he lost his savings _
about dlrs 80,000 _ in Russia's financial crisis last summer.
	   ``All my money is gone,'' he told Bunte magazine.
	   The financial turmoil in August sent the Moscow bank where he
had his account into bankruptcy, he said. Because of the loss, he
said he hasn't been able to pay the employees at his personally
financed foundation for months either.
	   ``You know, I'm not really as rich as many in the West think,''
he said. ``The 'new rich' here in Moscow often spend more in one
night than I earn in a whole year.''
	   Gorbachev said he hoped to sign a lucrative deal for a new book
he is working on, which he hopes to have published for the 10th
anniversary of German reunification next October.
