<SLUG> BC-Bosnia-Explosive </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NATO-led troops help destroying explosive ordnance
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SARAJEVO, Bosnia-Herzegovina (AP) _ Italian troops serving in
the NATO-led peacekeeping force in Bosnia are helping the Bosnian
Serb army destroying ammunition and explosives previously collected
from civilians, NATO officials said Tuesday.
	   The goal of the operation, that started a few days ago under the
codename ``Elisa,'' is to dispose of large amounts of ammunition
that has been stockpiled at Bosnian Serb Army sites around their
stronghold of Pale near Sarajevo, said NATO spokesman Maj. Glenn
Chamberlain.
	   The Bosnian Serb army does not have enough ordnance disposal
experts to do the job by itself. NATO has sent two teams to help
destroy ``large amounts'' of ammunition and explosives, Chamberlain
said.
	   Much of the ammunition and explosives are stored in poor
conditions and has been sitting there for some time, he said.
	   ac/ad/rr
