<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-World Cup-Thieves, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Three Romanians jailed for posing as police during World Cup
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS in 4th graf that thieves were dressed as civilians &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SAINT-ETIENNE, France (AP) _ Three Romanian men have been jailed
for a year for robbing soccer fans while posing as police officers
during the World Cup.
	   The thieves, identified as Dimitri Ionita, Florin Popeanu and
Adrian Prodan, were sentenced late Monday night. They are all in
their 30s and known criminals, police said.
	   All three pleaded guilty to robbing fans after stopping them in
the street for what they said were police searches for drugs.
	   Passing themselves off as plain-clothes officers, the thieves
quickly flashed papers which their victims presumed were police
identity cards, the victims said.
	   Arrested June 19 after a match between Spain and Paraguay in
this town in central France, the three men were carrying South
American and Spanish currency.
	   When ordered to identify themselves, they produced false Italian
papers.
	   The men were also banned from returning to France for 10 years.
	   (parf-ip)
