<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Spurs-Freund </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
German star take vacation before joining Spurs
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Tottenham has allowed new signing Steffen Freund
to take a two-week vacation before the German international
midfielder plays his first game in the Premier League on Jan. 9.
	   The experienced midfielder has joined Spurs for 750,000 pounds
(dlrs 1.25 million) and is expected to make his debut against
Sheffield Wednesday.
	   Spurs manager George Graham allowed the 28-year-old former
Schalke and Borussia Dortmund player to go ahead with his vacation
plans, which had already been arranged to coincide with the
Bundesliga's annual mid-winter break.
	   ``It will be a couple of weeks before he's here but he'll soon
become a big favorite with the fans,'' Graham said on Tuesday.
	   ``I'm delighted to have signed him and he will be coming here to
do what he is good at _ winning the ball and then passing it.
	   ``There is great enthusiasm running through the side now but we
still need something more to make sure the improvement continues,''
Graham said the day after his team crushed Everton 4-1 with three
goals from striker Chris Armstrong.
	   ``It's something that the top teams like Manchester United,
Arsenal and Chelsea all have, players who dominate the midfield and
make others play.
	   ``This guy has all the experience in the world with Borussia
Dortmund in their European campaigns and with Germany as part of
their squad in Euro 96.''
	   Freund, who has played 21 times for Germany, had to pull out of
last summer's World Cup in France because of a calf muscle injury.
	   (rjm) 	   
</TEXT>
