<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Vatican-Ticket Increase </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vatican Museums raise entrance fees
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   VATICAN CITY (AP) _ The Vatican Museums, which include access to
the Sistine Chapel, are raising entrance fees from 15,000 lire
(dlrs 9) to 18,000 dire (dlrs 10.90).
	   The Vatican said Tuesday the higher ticket prices will go into
effect on Saturday, the first day in 1999 when the museums are
open.
	   The museums already are one of the most-visited attractions in
Italy, and crowds are expected to grow in the Holy Year in 2000,
when an extra 20 million visitors are expected in Rome.
	   Prices of discount tickets, for religious pilgrims and students,
will rise from 10,000 lire (dlrs 6) to 12,000 lire (dlrs 7.25).
	   Entrance will remain free on the last Sunday of every month,
unless those days correspond with Vatican holidays. Entrance is
also free on Sept. 27, World Tourism Day.
	   The Vatican attributed the rising ticket prices to higher
operating costs.
	   (fd-ek)
</TEXT>
