<HEADLINE>
Police kill nine Maoist rebels in Nepal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) _ A three-hour gunbattle between police and
Maoist rebels left nine guerrillas dead in western Nepal, police
said Tuesday.
	   Police shot and killed seven rebels Monday in the village of
Kerabari, 75 miles (120 kilometers) west of Katmandu, the Nepalese
