relief aid deliveries. Pickup 5th graf pvs, `The rebel ...' &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   FREETOWN, Sierra Leone (AP) _ Rebel forces battling to oust
President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah have taken control of the central town
of Makeni, defense force officers said Tuesday.
	   Makeni, a strategic town about 120 kilometers (75 miles)
northeast of the capital, Freetown, was the scene of recent heavy
fighting.
	   Rebel fighters battling a West African coalition army known as
ECOMOG succeeded in pushing the defense force into a ``tactical
retreat,'' according to an ECOMOG statement.
	   Sierra Leone's Foreign Minister Sam Banya on Monday said
virtually the entire population of several thousand people fled
Makeni.
	   The United Nations World Food Program on Tuesday warned the
escalating hostilities could jeopardize relief programs in the
country's interior.
	   Food aid shipments to Makeni and other areas have been halted,
affected feeding and distribution programs for close to 24,000
people, WFP said in a statement.
	   ``Those most likely to be affected by the lack of food are
displaced persons who were living in camps and urban areas in the
north and the east,'' said Sierra Leone's WFP representative
Patrick Buckley.
	   Fighting in the eastern Kono region may have forced as many as
40,000 to flee their homes, Buckley said.
