<SLUG> BC-France-Eiffel Tower </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Eiffel Tower announces top record six million visitors
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ A record 6 million people visited the Eiffel Tower
this year, and most were foreigners, tower officials announced
Tuesday.
	   The Eiffel Tower, France's most popular monument, drew twice as
many visitors as the Empire State Building in New York and the
Tower of Tokyo, both of which attracted about three million
visitors.
	   About 80 percent of the tower's visitors were non-French,
including 13 percent from North America, officials said.
	   Last year 5.7 million visited the century-old Eiffel Tower.
Built from 9,700 tons of pig-iron, soaring 1,050 feet above the
City of Light and illuminated by 10,000 light bulbs, it has become
the symbol of a nation and its people.
	   Sixty tons of paint are needed to repaint the tower every seven
years and two tons of paper are required to print yearly admission
tickets.
	   The tower is twice as popular as France's second most visited
monument _ the Louvre museum _ which attracts 3 million visitors
yearly. The Chateau de Versailles comes in third with 2.3 million
visitors.
	   (ma-cb)
</TEXT>
