r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Russia-NewMiG     12-29 0294
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-New MiG </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russia unveils new version of MiG fighter
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A new generation of one of the world's most
successful military aircraft, the MiG fighter jet, rolled off the
production line Tuesday, a news agency reported.
	   The new MiG-29SMT is an retrofitted version of the standard
MiG-29 fighter, offering more sophisticated instrumentation, longer
range and greater combat load capacity, ITAR-Tass said, quoting the
plane's chief designer, Valery Novikov.
	   ``The overhauling of the MiG-29, which will raise its combat
efficiency eight times, will help to raise the striking potential
of the Russian air force many times,'' Novikov said.
	   The MiG-29 was first produced for the Soviet air force in 1985.
It was the latest version of MiG fighters that had been the
standard attack jet for the Soviet Union and its allies since their
introduction in 1949.
	   The Russian Defense Ministry _ clearly lacking the resources to
develop a new plane _ decided early this year to overhaul 150 to
180 MiG-29s into the more sophisticated SMT version, ITAR-Tass
said. The planes are expected to be in service until 2020, when a
new plane is expected to be developed.
	   Already, funding shortages have held back the retrofitting
program. The Defense Ministry originally anticipated completing 10
to 15 of the new planes this year, rather than a single prototype.
	   Plans now call for 24 of the modernized planes to be completed
next year.
	   The main changes in the new MiG include additional fuel tanks,
which will extend its cruising range up to 3,500 kilometers (2,175
miles); a mid-air refueling system; new avionics and
instrumentation; and a combat load that has been increased from
three to five tons.
	   (ml)
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
