<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Fluminense-Berti,0195 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Brazil's Fluminese buys Italian midfielder
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) _ Italy's veteran midfielder Nicolas
Berti is headed for Brazil to join Fluminese, a team official said
Tuesday.
	   The 31-year-old Berti, who played last season with England's
Tottenham Hotspur, will arrive Saturday to sign a two-year contract
with the Rio club, Vice President Francisco Horta said in a radio
interview.
	   Berti reportedly will earn 40,000 reals (dlrs 33,000) a month
during the two-year contract. Financing is expected to come in part
from a deal being finalized with Brazil's FonteCindam investment
bank.
	   Berti, who played for Italy in the World Cups of 1990 and 1994,
is part of a rebuilding campaign by Fluminense, a national champion
in 1984 that fell to the third division last season.
	   The club also is pursuing at least three other foreign players:
Belgian goalie Preud'homme and Portuguese stars Rui Costa and
Peixe.
	   Fluminese players return from vacation next week for pre-season
training. The first official game is against Santos on Jan. 23 for
the Rio-Sao Paulo Tournament.
</TEXT>
