<SLUG> BC-Italy-Cell Phone License </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Rome takes step towards fourth cell phone license
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ The Italian government on Tuesday moved one step
closer to assigning a fourth cellular phone license with a request
to the premier to get the groundwork going for the bidding process.
	   The communications ministry said Minister Salvatore Cardinale
asked for a ministerial committee to be set up to choose advisers
and oversee the bidding process. A fourth license is generally
expected to be assigned in mid-1999.
	   Current holders of Italian cellular phone licenses are Telecom
Italia Mobile SpA; Omnitel, controlled by Olivetti SpA and
Mannesmann AG, and the WIND consortium, made up of Deutsche
Telekom, France Telecom and the Italian electricity group ENEL.
	   Swisscom AG, the Picienne consortium and the Telon consortium
have all expressed an interest in competing in the bidding process.
	   (fd)
</TEXT>
