<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-British Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chelsea and United tie 0-0
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Tore Andre Flo and Gianfranco Zola missed four
good chances as Chelsea squandered a chance to regain top place in
the Premier League from Aston Villa on Tuesday after a 0-0 tie with
Manchester United.
	   Flo had three opportunities in the first half while the
ever-dangerous Zola had two. The experienced Italian got round
United goalkeeper Peter Schmeichel only to roll the ball wide nine
minutes from the end.
	   The goal-less tie means that Chelsea remains second, two points
behind Villa after 20 of the 38 games in the campaign and United is
fourth.
	   In another Premier League game, Leeds and Wimbledon tied 2-2.
	   Flo headed Zola's corner wide and then shot wide of the near
post from five meters as Chelsea, who tied 1-1 at Old Trafford 12
days ago, created the early chances at Stamford Bridge.
	   In the 21st minute, Zola dribbled skilfully past United's Dutch
defender Jaap Stam only for Schmeichel to save his well-struck shot
with a brilliant one-handed stop. The ball rolled to Flo who
stabbed it wide with the 'keeper grounded.
	   Zola should have scored just before half time when he
intercepted a poor pass from Roy Keane but Schmeichel raced off his
line to grab the ball at his feet.
	   For United, Andy Cole wasted a chance when he hesitated in front
of goal and Keane fired too high from 20 meters early in the second
half. Although Alex Ferguson's team had more of the play after the
break, it failed to create any clear cut openings.
	   At Elland Road, Leeds twice took the lead against the Dons who
hit back with two equalizer.
	   After Bruno Ribeiro had fired David O'Leary's team ahead, Robbie
Earle leveled and, after David Hopkin has restored Leeds'
advantage, Karl Cort replied to earn Roy Kinnear's team a point.
	   (rjm)	   
</TEXT>
