<HEADLINE>
New Basque premier elected with backing of ETA-linked party
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS overline to reflect election. Picks up 2nd graf pvs &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VITORIA, Spain (AP) _ A moderate pro-Basque independence
candidate was Tuesday elected premier of the new regional
government with the help of deputies linked to the armed separatist
group ETA.
	   Juan Jose, 2nd graf pvs
</TEXT>
