<SLUG> BC-Sports-Olympic Bribes-Glance,0180 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With BC-Sports-Olympic Bribes
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   The members of the special commission appointed by U.S. Olympic
Committee President Bill Hybl to look into allegations of bribes by
Salt Lake City officials to win the 2002 Winter Olympics:
	   _ Chairman George Mitchell. Former U.S. Senate majority leader.
Helped broker peace accord in Northern Ireland. Informal adviser to
President Bill Clinton on impeachment. Also serves as chairman of
the standing USOC ethics committee.
	   _ Vice Chairman Donald Fehr. Executive director and general
counsel of the U.S. Major League Baseball Players Association.
Member of USOC board of directors.
	   _ Ken Duberstein. President of Duberstein and Co., Washington
D.C. Former chief of staff to President Reagan, and a vice-chairman
of USOC ethics committee.
	   _ Roberta Cooper Ramo, attorney of Albuquerque, New Mexico, past
president of the American Bar Association.
	   _ Jeff Benz, at-large member of the USOC Athletes Advisory
Council and an attorney in San Francisco.
</TEXT>
