<HEADLINE>
Martinsen captures third cross country World Cup event
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KITZBUEHEL, Austria (AP) _ Norway's Bente Martinsen Tuesday won
her third straight Skiing cross-country World Cup sprint, beating
Slovenia's Andreja Mali in the final.
	   Germany's Peter Schlickenrieder captured the men's race when
Sweden's Thobias Fredriksson fell in the final of the event held at
night.
	   In his semifinal, Schlickenrieder beat Austria's Christian
Hoffmann, who had captured Olympic bronze in the 50-kilometer
marathon.
	   Fredriksson beat Austria's Marc Mayer in his semifinal as 5,000
spectators watched the event raced through the center of
Kitzbuehel.
	   Norway's Anne-Kristen Marken finished third in the women's event
and Italy's Karin Moroder was fourth.
	   Schlickenrieder's victory came after he was disqualified and
fell in his last two sprint events.
