<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-New Zealand-Quake </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fairly strong quake hits New Zealand but no damage reported
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WELLINGTON, New Zealand (AP) _ A moderately strong earthquake
with a magnitude of 5.7 shook New Zealand's North Island on
Wednesday, but there were no early reports of major damage or
injuries.
	   The Institute of Geological and Nuclear Sciences said the quake
was centered 5 kilometers (3 miles) south of Rotorua and struck at
3:45 a.m. (1645 GMT Tuesday).
	   It was felt as far away as Wellington, 400 kilometers (250
miles) to the south. 	   
</TEXT>
