<SLUG> BC-AP News Digest,1047 </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _GREECE-CYPRUS. President cancels deployment of Russian
missiles.
	   _COLOMBIA-REBELS. Rebels attack police post, battle militias.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   SAN`A, Yemen _ Yemeni troops exchange gunfire with Islamic
extremists holding 16 Western tourists hostage, ending the
kidnapping with four hostages and three assailants dead.
YEMEN-KIDNAPPING. Recap expected by 0100 GMT. By Ahmad Al-Haj.
	   ALSO MOVED: YEMEN-ISLAMIC JIHAD. Islamic group has been friend
and foe of government.
	   BAGHDAD, Iraq _ Iraq defiantly says its aircraft are flying in
the ``no-fly'' zones patrolled by U.S. and British warplanes and
its anti-aircraft batteries remain ready to fire on allied planes.
IRAQ. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. By Louis Meixler. AP Photo
LON109.
	   ALSO MOVED: US-IRAQ. U.S., Britain plan continued enforcement of
Iraqi no-fly zone. AP Photos WXS102-105, WX116-117.
	   SYDNEY, Australia _ Two inquiries will be held into the deadly
Sydney-to-Hobart yacht race following reports that race organizers
knew of the potential danger 24 hours before the fleet was
decimated by a massive storm. AUSTRALIA-DEADLY YACHT RACE. Recap
expected by 0200 GMT; also moving on sports lines. By Tony Harper.
	   PHNOM PENH, Cambodia _ Two Khmer Rouge leaders who say they are
``very sorry'' for genocide remain in the capital on Wednesday,
free from trial and still refusing to accept any responsibility for
their movement's atrocities. CAMBODIA-KHMER ROUGE. Recap expected
by 0500 GMT. By Chris Fontaine. AP Photos CTO101-103, PHN101-107.
	   JERUSALEM _ Israel's national election is months away, but
already the biggest campaign issue is an event that hasn't happened
in a place yet to be determined: Palestinian independence.
ANALYSIS-ISRAEL-STATEHOOD SCRAMBLE. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Laura
King.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _ISRAEL-POLITICS. More Netanyahu allies turn against the prime
minister. AP Photos JRL102-105.
	   _ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. Israel threatens to close Palestinian
airport over security violation.
	   WASHINGTON _ House members appointed to prosecute President Bill
Clinton emerge from their first strategy session with plans to call
witnesses in a historic impeachment trial. But Senate leaders
oppose the idea. US-CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT. Recap expected by 0200
GMT. By Larry Margasak. AP Photo WX119-120, ACAP104.
	   ALSO: US-JOHNSON WREATH. Clinton honors only other president to
be impeached. AP Photo GNV101.
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ While diplomats try to shore up the shaky
Kosovo truce, Yugoslavia is urging the United Nations to crack down
on the international support network for the province's ethnic
Albanian rebels. YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. By
Veselin Toshkov. AP Photos BEL101-104.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _KOSOVO-DRESS REHEARSAL. Residents fear fighting is precursor of
fiercer battles to come.
	   _US-YUGOSLAVIA. U.S. lawmakers urge Yugoslav leader to step down
peacefully.
	   NICOSIA, Cyprus _ President Glafcos Clerides cancels plans to
deploy controversial, Russian-made missiles in this island nation.
GREECE-CYPRUS. Lead has moved. By Alex Efty. AP Photos NIC101-104.
	   LAKKA TOWN, Sierra Leone _ In this West African country where
thousands of defenseless villagers have been mutilated by brutal
rebels, Red Cross doctors have resurrected a World War I-era
surgical operation to give hope to the growing ranks of amputees.
SIERRA LEONE-MUTILATED HOPE. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Glenn
McKenzie.
	   ALSO MOVED: SIERRA LEONE. Rebels threaten to attack capital
within two days.
	   KAMPALA, Uganda _ The presidents of Uganda and Rwanda say their
forces will continue to support a rebellion in neighboring Congo
until security along their borders is assured. UGANDA-RWANDA-CONGO.
Lead has moved. By Henry Wasswa.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _CONGO-REBELS. Rebels push into northwestern Congo.
	   _REPUBLIC OF CONGO-BORDER PACT. Neighboring Congos sign
non-aggression pact.
	   LUANDA, Angola _ The army drives back a rebel offensive, killing
30 rebels and capturing two armored vehicles. ANGOLA-FIGHTING. Has
moved. By Casimiro Siona.
	   ALSO MOVED: UN-ANGOLA. United Nations pushes for access to plane
crash site.
	   BOGOTA, Colombia _ Just a week before peace talks are to begin,
leftist rebels attack a police post and battle pro-government
paramilitary fighters. COLOMBIA-REBELS. AP Photo BOG101.
	   SAO PAULO, Brazil _ The government announces that seven
kidnappers convicted in the 1989 abduction of a leading Brazilian
businessman can complete their sentences in their home countries.
BRAZIL-KIDNAPPERS. Has moved. By Stan Lehman. AP Photo SAO101.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: On Thursday, the European Union sets the rates at
which the euro will be valued against other currencies in Brussels,
Belgium; An around-the-world balloon team hopes to start its
journey from Alice Springs, Australia.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	   CONAKRY, Guinea _ In Africa, nations are arguing over
government-sponsored brutalities of recent decades. But in Guinea,
some people say the question has become whether there should be
memories of any sort about former President Sekou Toure's brutal
regime. FEA-GUINEA-MEMORIES OF TERROR. Upcoming. By Tim Sullivan.
AP Photos NY333-NY334. GRAPHIC GUINEA PRISON.
