<HEADLINE>
Hasek, Jagr continue to lead NHL World All-Stars
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW YORK (AP) _ Goaltender Dominik Hasek of the Buffalo Sabres
and winger Jaromir Jagr of the Pittsburgh Penguins lead the voting
for the National Hockey League World All-Star team.
	   In results released Tuesday, Hasek ranks first among the World
All-Stars with 206,698 votes, followed by Jagr, who ranks second
overall with 188,683 votes.
	   Joining Hasek and Jagr as leaders in the race for starting
positions are Detroit Red Wings defensemen Nicklas Lidstrom
(164,032) and Uwe Krupp (99,338), Red Wings center Sergei Fedorov
(94,457) and Anaheim Mighty Ducks winger Teemu Selanne (155,414).
	   The final results for this World team balloting will be
announced Jan. 6.
	   The top players representing Canada and United States will
comprise the North America team. The latest vote results for the
North American team are to be released Wednesday with the final
totals announced Jan. 7.
</TEXT>
